'All is well,'
'It is a gift that I bring you from the Lady of Rivendell,'
'In a high chamber of the Burg,'
'A little people, but of great worth are the Shire-folk,'
'This is an evil door,'
'We seek one Aragorn son of Arathorn, and we heard that he was in Rohan.'
'That is all of our kindred that could be gathered in haste; but the brethren Elladan and Elrohir have ridden with us, desiring to go to the war. We rode as swiftly as we might when your summons came.'
'What is that that you bear, kinsman?'
'She wrought it in secret, and long was the making. But she also sends word to you: The days now are short. Either our hope cometh, or all hopes end. Therefore I send thee what I have made for thee. Fare well, Elfstone!'
'Little do they know of our long labour for the safekeeping of their borders, and yet I grudge it not.'
'and my death lies beyond it. I will dare to pass it nonetheless; but no horse will enter.'
